{"parentUuid":"84d840c9-0cb3-44e6-9cf0-2337876acef4","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\acodu\\dev\\dashboard_mictlan\\.claude\\worktrees\\eloquent-shtern","sessionId":"b887e195-06d9-4ec4-8b4e-c94ecf98a85e","version":"2.1.51","gitBranch":"claude/eloquent-shtern","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MRak7amMWNp45p8wRM6Af7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An **artifact** is a piece of generated content that Claude displays in a **dedicated side panel** alongside the chat, rather than inline in the conversation.\n\n## What counts as an artifact:\n- 📄 **Text documents** – essays, emails, reports\n- 💻 **Code snippets** – scripts, functions, full files\n- 🌐 **Website designs** – HTML/CSS/JS that renders live in the panel\n- 📊 **Other structured content** – markdown docs, SVGs, etc.\n\n## Why it's useful:\n- Keeps the **chat clean** — long code or documents don't clutter the conversation\n- Provides a **dedicated view** where you can read, copy, or interact with the content\n- For web content, it can **render live** so you see the actual result\n- Easy to **iterate** — Claude can update the artifact while keeping the conversation separate\n\nEssentially, it's Claude's way of saying *\"here's the thing I made\"* in its own window, so you can work with it more easily."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":23424,"cache_read_input_tokens":14189,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":23424},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CYnmnUU7gp596XaWxFdLc","type":"assistant","uuid":"e9d3ba34-d805-4444-ab38-b4fab3a13445","timestamp":"2026-03-07T00:28:20.809Z"}
